The family of the late Nigerian juju singer, Dayo Kujore has announced the burial plans of the entertainer. The Kujore’s announced that the singer will be buried on the January 28, 2022. The veteran juju singer died on January 10, 2022 at the age of 69. He was confirmed dead at the Lagos State Teaching Hospital where he was receiving treatment for an undisclosed ailment. Yiaga to hold town hall meeting on Electoral Bill Former FUT Minna VC, Prof. Daniya, dies at 72 The singer was known for creating the Soko Tune in the Juju music genre. His daughter who is also a singer, Ayinke Dayo Kujore, took to her Instagram page to announce the burial plans. The wake keep service is set to hold on the January 27, at his compound at Igbore Robiyan Village at 4:00pm. The burial service takes place on January 28, at Emmanuel Africa Church, Igbore Robiyan. His daughter further noted that other details of the burial will be announced later. Ayinke Dayo wrote at the the end of the announcement, “Love you forever daddy mi.”  See post below: 